    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Press Release Issued at Nanking on June 5</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d506</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">506</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-06-05T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued at Nanking on June 5</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Nanking</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-05">June 5, 1946</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Committee of Three has directed the movement of an advance Section of
                    Executive Headquarters to Changchun, there to get established <pb facs="0989" n="977" xml:id="pg_977"/> in preparation for carrying out whatever
                    agreements may be reached for the cessation of hostilities. Brigadier General
                    Henry A. Byroade will be the senior American Officer in this Advance Section.
                    Brigadier General Thomas S. Timberman will temporarily take over General
                    Byroade’s duties in Peiping.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
